match

public final Substitution match(AtomicFormula atom)
Matches this atomic formula with an other specified atomic formula. Two atomic formulas match if they have the same predicate symbol and arity and each arguments are pairwise unifiable. Note, called match does not modify the parameters of this method.

Parameters:
atom - the atomic formula to match with.
Returns:
The substitution that defines the binding constraints needed to match this atomic formula with the other atomic formula or null if no binding constraints allows to match the two atomic formulas.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if atom == null or sigma == null.
See Also:
Term.unify(Term, Substitution)

match

public final Substitution match(AtomicFormula atom,
                                Substitution sigma)
Matches this atomic formula with an other specified atomic formula by taking into account a specified set of binding constraints. Two atomic formulas match if they have the same predicate symbol and arity and each arguments are pairwise unifiable. Note, called match does not modify the parameters of this method.

Parameters:
atom - the atomic formula to match with.
sigma - the substitution containing the binding constraints.
Returns:
The substitution that defines the binding constraints needed to match this atomic formula with the other atomic formula or null if no binding constraints allows to match the two atomic formulas.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if atom == null or sigma == null.
See Also:
Term.unify(Term, Substitution)
